    <section class="wiring-problems">
      <h2>Dangerous Wiring Problems We Replace</h2>
      <div class="problem-grid">
        <div class="wiring-problem critical">
          <h3>‚ö†Ô∏è Knob & Tube Wiring</h3>
          <p><strong>Age:</strong> 1880s-1940s</p>
          <p><strong>Dangers:</strong> Fire hazard, no grounding, inadequate for modern loads, insurance issues</p>
          <p><strong>Signs:</strong> Ceramic knobs and tubes in basement/attic, cloth-wrapped wiring, two-prong outlets only</p>
          <p class="urgency critical">CRITICAL - Replace immediately for safety</p>
        </div>

        <div class="wiring-problem high">
          <h3>üî• Aluminum Wiring</h3>
          <p><strong>Age:</strong> 1960s-1970s</p>
          <p><strong>Dangers:</strong> Overheating connections, fire risk, corrosion, loose connections</p>
          <p><strong>Signs:</strong> "AL" markings on wires, warm outlets/switches, flickering lights</p>
          <p class="urgency high">HIGH RISK - Schedule replacement soon</p>
        </div>

        <div class="wiring-problem medium">
          <h3>‚ö° Cloth-Wrapped Wiring</h3>
          <p><strong>Age:</strong> 1930s-1950s</p>
          <p><strong>Dangers:</strong> Deteriorating insulation, exposed conductors, shock hazard</p>
          <p><strong>Signs:</strong> Fabric insulation, brittle wiring, frequent electrical issues</p>
          <p class="urgency medium">MEDIUM RISK - Plan replacement</p>
        </div>

        <div class="wiring-problem medium">
          <h3>üè† Insufficient Wiring Capacity</h3>
          <p><strong>Age:</strong> Pre-1960s homes</p>
          <p><strong>Problems:</strong> Frequent breaker trips, inadequate outlets, extension cord dependency</p>
          <p><strong>Signs:</strong> Only 60-100 amp service, few outlets per room, no GFCI protection</p>
          <p class="urgency medium">UPGRADE NEEDED - For modern living</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="rewiring-process">
      <h2>Our Whole House Rewiring Process</h2>
      <div class="process-steps">
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">1</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Comprehensive Electrical Inspection (Day 1)</h3>
            <p>Licensed electrician performs detailed assessment of existing wiring, electrical panel, outlets, and switches. We identify safety hazards, code violations, and create a comprehensive rewiring plan with timeline and costs.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">2</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Permits & Planning (Days 2-5)</h3>
            <p>We obtain all necessary electrical permits, coordinate with utility companies, plan wire routing to minimize wall damage, and schedule work to minimize disruption to your daily life.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">3</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Electrical Panel & Service Upgrade (Day 6)</h3>
            <p>If needed, we upgrade your electrical panel to 200 amp service, install new main breaker, update grounding system, and ensure adequate capacity for modern electrical demands.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">4</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Complete Home Rewiring (Days 7-14)</h3>
            <p>Room-by-room rewiring using modern copper wiring, GFCI and AFCI protection, updated outlets and switches, proper grounding, and minimal wall damage with professional repair.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">5</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Testing & Final Inspection (Day 15)</h3>
            <p>Complete system testing, city electrical inspection, final walkthrough with homeowner, warranty documentation, and cleanup of all work areas.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="why-choose-rewiring">
      <h2>Why Choose Our Whole House Rewiring Service</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="benefit">
          <h3>üèÜ Rewiring Specialists</h3>
          <p>Over 15 years specializing in whole house rewiring projects. We've rewired hundreds of Omaha homes and understand the unique challenges of older Nebraska homes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit">
          <h3>üè† Minimal Disruption Method</h3>
          <p>Advanced techniques to minimize wall damage and disruption. We work room-by-room so you can continue living in your home during the rewiring process.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit">
          <h3>üí∞ Transparent Pricing</h3>
          <p>Fixed-price contracts with no surprises. We provide detailed estimates covering all materials, labor, permits, and cleanup. Financing options available.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit">
          <h3>üìã Complete Permit Service</h3>
          <p>We handle all permits, inspections, and utility coordination. You don't have to deal with city bureaucracy - we manage everything for you.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit">
          <h3>üõ°Ô∏è 10-Year Warranty</h3>
          <p>Industry-leading 10-year warranty on all rewiring work. We stand behind our craftsmanship and use only premium materials and components.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit">
          <h3>üîß Code Compliance Experts</h3>
          <p>All work exceeds current electrical codes. We ensure your rewiring project will pass inspection and meet insurance requirements.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="rewiring-benefits">
      <h2>Benefits of Whole House Rewiring</h2>
      <div class="benefits-grid">
        <div class="benefit-item">
          <h3>üî• Improved Safety</h3>
          <p>Eliminate fire hazards from old wiring, add GFCI protection in bathrooms and kitchens, install AFCI protection for bedrooms, and ensure proper grounding throughout your home.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-item">
          <h3>üí° Modern Convenience</h3>
          <p>Add outlets where you need them, install USB charging outlets, upgrade to dimmer switches, add dedicated circuits for appliances, and eliminate extension cord dependency.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-item">
          <h3>üí∞ Increased Home Value</h3>
          <p>Rewiring can increase home value by $5,000-$15,000, makes your home more attractive to buyers, satisfies insurance requirements, and eliminates buyer concerns about electrical systems.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-item">
          <h3>‚ö° Better Performance</h3>
          <p>Consistent power throughout your home, no more flickering lights, stable voltage for electronics, and adequate capacity for modern appliances and devices.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-item">
          <h3>üè† Insurance Compliance</h3>
          <p>Many insurance companies require rewiring for homes with old wiring, can reduce insurance premiums, eliminates coverage restrictions, and provides peace of mind.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-item">
          <h3>üîå Smart Home Ready</h3>
          <p>Prepare your home for smart devices, adequate power for home automation, proper grounding for sensitive electronics, and future-proof electrical infrastructure.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
